         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>93</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4 #a5 #a6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Ebenso ist, nachdem (er sich) vom Gesetz (abgewandt) und (der Gesetzlosigkeit) zugewandt hat, der Tor, (wenn er in die Gewalt des Todes gelangt ist), betrübt wie einer [scil. ein Fuhrmann], dessen Achse gebrochen ist.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">In the same way, the fool, after (he has turned away) from the law and has turned towards (lawlessness), is sad like someone [i.e. a carter] whose axle has broken.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>157</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a7"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">Das Nichtzutuende wird wiederum getan.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">What is not to be done, on the other hand, is done.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>229</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:krause1952"/><citedRange>132</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>17</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">(Der aber ist Träger des Gesetzes), der im Gesetz nicht nachlässig ist.</seg><seg type="sec_transl" resp="TI">(He, however, is the bearer of the Law), who is not negligent in the Law.</seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>177</citedRange></bibl></seg></choice></p>
